problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in philosophy would. What is the molecular weight of N-[(3-chlorocyclohexyl)methyl]-2-fluoroethanamine?
Answer (numerical number):
gpt_response:
The molecular weight of N-[(3-chlorocyclohexyl)methyl]-2-fluoroethanamine can be calculated by adding up the atomic weights of all the atoms in the molecule. 

N = 14.01
C = 12.01
Cl = 35.45
H = 1.01
F = 19.00

(1 x 14.01) + (10 x 12.01) + (1 x 35.45) + (2 x 1.01) + (1 x 19.00) = 243.67

Therefore, the molecular weight of N-[(3-chlorocyclohexyl)methyl]-2-fluoroethanamine is 243.67 g/mol.
